  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tanzania population movement 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since President Pierre Nkurunziza launched his controversial bid for a third term in office. (Burundi s constitution only allows the president to be elected twice) there has been an escalation in pre-election violence. Confrontations between protesters and the police started on Sunday 26th April. The violence has led to more than 92 000 people fleeing to the neighbouring countries of Rwanda ( approx 24 000) DRC (9 796) Uganda (5 952) and Tanzania (47 929). While no urgent humanitarian needs have yet emerged in Burundi protests continue and fears of escalating violence are apparent. Whilst a DREF has been launched for Rwanda the IFRC launched an Emergency Appeal for Tanzania for CHF 1 026 583 targeting 20 000 vulnerable beneficiaries (women with young children pregnant or lactating). The response will focus on provision of emergency health screening and first aid water sanitation hygiene promotion and shelter.</narrative>
  </description>
